-- Kansas City Board of Trade to Extend Pit-Trading Hours for Grain
-- B y   T o n y   C .   D r e i b u s
-- 2012-06-08T17:18:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-08/kansas-city-board-of-trade-to-extend-pit-trading-hours-for-grain.html
The Kansas City Board of Trade will
extend its open-outcry trading for grain contracts by 45 minutes
to 2 p.m. Monday through Friday, spokeswoman Shelia Summers said
by telephone today. The close, which is currently at 1:15 p.m.,
will match pit trading on the Chicago Board of Trade.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony C. Dreibus in Chicago at 
 tdreibus@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
